It must be pointed out, in fact, that millions of people living there are completely out of touch with reality, unaware of the outside world.
Their lives consist in grovelling before a leader who tells them each morning that the entire world wants to overrun them.
In North Korea, we are confronted with a world that would appear to be very close to that of George Orwell.
